==English==
===Verb===
'''to [[crawl]] [[with]]'''

#{{transitive}} {{idiom}} To contain swarms or large numbers of (something, especially insects or people); to have in great [[number]]s or [[multitude]]s.
#:''The kitchen was '''crawling with''' cockroaches.''
#:''The scene of the incident was '''crawling with''' reporters for days afterwards.''

====Usage notes====
*'''To crawl with''' is usually used with [[continuous]] tenses ("crawling with").